---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';

const title = 'How Meta Ads Actually Work in 2026: Andromeda, GEM, and the CTC Canon, Checked Against Independent Experts';
const description = 'A breakdown of the CTC Canon framework for Meta advertising in 2026, Andromeda, GEM, budget liquidity, never turning off an ad, checked against Jon Loomer, Andrew Foxwell, Meta\'s own engineering blog, and 12 years of my own paid social experience.';
const pubDate = 'July 10, 2026';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
		<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
			"@context": "https://schema.org",
			"@type": "Article",
			"headline": title,
			"description": description,
			"url": Astro.url.href,
			"mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": Astro.url.href },
			"image": new URL('/og-default.png', Astro.site).toString(),
			"author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Jack Maguire", "url": Astro.site?.toString() },
			"publisher": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Jack Maguire", "url": Astro.site?.toString() },
			"datePublished": "2026-07-10",
			"dateModified": "2026-07-10"
		})} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<main>
			<!-- HERO -->
			<section class="hero">
				<div class="wrap">
					<p class="eyebrow">Account audit &middot; Meta advertising &middot; {pubDate}</p>
					<h1>Your Meta account is still built for an algorithm that doesn't exist anymore.</h1>
					<p class="hero-sub">
						Common Thread Collective published a framework in June 2026 called the CTC Canon. I checked
						it against Meta's own engineering blog and independent experts with no methodology to
						sell, then against 12 years of running paid social myself. Most of it holds up. Some of it
						needs a caveat nobody's saying out loud.
					</p>
					<div class="hero-stat">
						<span class="stat-number">10,000x</span>
						<span class="stat-label">the jump in ad-retrieval model complexity Meta shipped with Andromeda, per Meta's own engineering blog. Your targeting settings matter less than they used to. Your creative matters more.</span>
					</div>
					<a href="#audit" class="hero-cta">Run the 90-second account audit &darr;</a>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- LENS -->
			<section class="lens">
				<div class="wrap">
					<p>
						<strong>Where this comes from:</strong> I ran Meta and TikTok spend at over $1M a month as
						Social Media Marketing Director at National Debt Relief, a regulated industry with legal
						and compliance in every campaign review. I built the CAPI integration, ran holdout-market
						incrementality tests, and watched the platform shift from an audience-targeting tool to
						something closer to a creative-scoring engine. This isn't an outside read. It's a lens
						from having defended a media plan to a CFO when the dashboard said one thing and the
						following week's delivery said another.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- AUDIT CHECKLIST -->
			<section id="audit" class="audit">
				<div class="wrap">
					<h2>The 90-second audit</h2>
					<p class="section-intro">Five habits that were correct in 2021 and are actively costing you money now. Check the ones that describe your account.</p>
					<ul class="audit-list">
						<li>
							<span class="audit-mark">01</span>
							<div>
								<p class="audit-claim">You've killed an ad because its 3-day ROAS looked bad.</p>
								<p class="audit-detail">Meta's own documentation says historical performance does not predict future delivery. If you're running cost controls, the algorithm already reduced that ad's allocation using signals you can't see. Turning it off removes optionality, it doesn't fix anything.</p>
							</div>
						</li>
						<li>
							<span class="audit-mark">02</span>
							<div>
								<p class="audit-claim">Your "creative volume" is ten ads with the same product shot and different headlines.</p>
								<p class="audit-detail">Andromeda clusters visually similar ads into one retrieval "ticket." Those ten ads count as one shot on goal, not ten. Real diversity of concept is the mechanism, not a style preference.</p>
							</div>
						</li>
						<li>
							<span class="audit-mark">03</span>
							<div>
								<p class="audit-claim">You get nervous when daily spend swings 30% and you cap the budget to smooth it out.</p>
								<p class="audit-detail">That swing is Meta's system spending aggressively in cheap inventory and pulling back in expensive moments. Budget liquidity is the feature. Smoothing it out is you fighting your own algorithm.</p>
							</div>
						</li>
						<li>
							<span class="audit-mark">04</span>
							<div>
								<p class="audit-claim">You don't know your Event Match Quality score, or it's below 7 out of 10.</p>
								<p class="audit-detail">Below that threshold GEM is optimizing against degraded data. Meta's April 2026 one-click CAPI rollout made this nearly free to fix. There's no excuse left for skipping it.</p>
							</div>
						</li>
						<li>
							<span class="audit-mark">05</span>
							<div>
								<p class="audit-claim">Your first move on underspend is loosening the ROAS target.</p>
								<p class="audit-detail">That's phase four of four. Phases one through three (creative expansion, bid surface expansion, underspend ad recovery) almost always solve it first. Relaxing the constraint is the last lever, not the first.</p>
							</div>
						</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="audit-result">Three or more checked? That's a structure problem, not a targeting problem. Keep reading, or skip to <a href="#contact">get a second pair of eyes</a>.</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- THE TWO SYSTEMS -->
			<section class="systems">
				<div class="wrap">
					<h2>The two systems running your account</h2>
					<div class="systems-grid">
						<div class="system-card">
							<h3>Andromeda</h3>
							<p class="system-role">Creative-first ad retrieval engine</p>
							<p>Evaluates creative attributes, user context, and behavioral signals to build a candidate set of eligible ads for every impression. Meta's engineering team describes a 10,000x increase in model complexity versus what came before, plus a 10x gain in inference efficiency.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="system-card">
							<h3>GEM</h3>
							<p class="system-role">Generative Evaluation Model, the ranking layer</p>
							<p>Unveiled by Meta in a November 2025 engineering paper. Reportedly the largest foundation model Meta has built for a recommendation system, trained at roughly GPT-4 scale. It decides what actually gets shown from Andromeda's candidate set.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<p class="systems-callout">Together: Meta is no longer audience-first. It's creative-first. Your targeting matters less than what you feed the system. <span class="attrib">Corroborated independently by Jon Loomer, who has covered Meta ads for a decade with no agency to sell.</span></p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- FOUR PHASE FRAMEWORK -->
			<section class="phases">
				<div class="wrap">
					<h2>Fixing underspend: work the phases in order</h2>
					<p class="section-intro">CTC's sequence for diagnosing delivery problems. Don't skip ahead.</p>
					<div class="phase-list">
						<div class="phase">
							<span class="phase-num">Phase 1</span>
							<h3>Creative expansion</h3>
							<p>Deploy genuinely different concepts into evergreen and active campaigns, not minor variations. This is almost always the right first move.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="phase">
							<span class="phase-num">Phase 2</span>
							<h3>Bid surface expansion</h3>
							<p>Duplicate evergreen campaigns into a different bidding mechanism (lowest cost, bid cap, cost cap) using the same creative pool. Accesses a different audience with no new segmentation.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="phase">
							<span class="phase-num">Phase 3</span>
							<h3>Underspend ad recovery</h3>
							<p>A dedicated campaign for ads that never got a fair shot, spend under 3x the CPA target. Give them another opportunity before writing them off.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="phase">
							<span class="phase-num">Phase 4</span>
							<h3>Constraint relaxation</h3>
							<p>Loosen the ROAS target or cost cap itself, only once the first three phases are exhausted and the business case justifies it. Last lever, not first.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- CORROBORATE / COMPLICATE -->
			<section class="verdicts">
				<div class="wrap">
					<h2>Checked against independent experts</h2>
					<p class="section-intro">Where the CTC Canon holds up against people with no framework to sell, and where it needs a caveat.</p>
					<div class="verdict-table">
						<div class="verdict-row verdict-head">
							<span>Claim</span>
							<span>Holds up</span>
							<span>Needs a caveat</span>
						</div>
						<div class="verdict-row">
							<span class="verdict-claim">Creative volume is the primary scaling lever</span>
							<span class="verdict-yes">Andrew Foxwell (Foxwell Founders, $500M+/mo managed) independently reached the same conclusion.</span>
							<span class="verdict-no">His own 2026 report found only 11% of agencies have a clear top-performing AI-generated ad. Volume without real diversity doesn't work.</span>
						</div>
						<div class="verdict-row">
							<span class="verdict-claim">Never turn off an ad</span>
							<span class="verdict-yes">Foxwell independently advises near-100% cost controls so the system, not a human, kills losers.</span>
							<span class="verdict-no">Cody Plofker (Jones Road Beauty) prefers bid caps over cost caps for tighter control. Not unanimous.</span>
						</div>
						<div class="verdict-row">
							<span class="verdict-claim">Clean signal (CAPI/EMQ) is a competitive moat</span>
							<span class="verdict-yes">Uncontested. Every named source treats 7+ EMQ as non-negotiable infrastructure.</span>
							<span class="verdict-no">Meta's April 2026 one-click CAPI rollout made this nearly free for everyone. The moat is shrinking fast.</span>
						</div>
						<div class="verdict-row">
							<span class="verdict-claim">Andromeda guarantees better performance</span>
							<span class="verdict-yes">Meta's own data shows measurable recall and quality gains platform-wide.</span>
							<span class="verdict-no">Jon Loomer: it "should improve performance, but it won't guarantee results." Bad performance is usually still a creative or offer problem.</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- THE JOB NOW -->
			<section class="summary">
				<div class="wrap">
					<h2>What the job actually is now</h2>
					<p>
						Three things, and this matches what worked in the accounts I ran. Set correct budget
						allocation with no artificial limits at the campaign level. Make sure the bid matches
						real unit economics, not a number that felt safe in a planning meeting. Keep feeding the
						machine genuinely new creative. That's most of the job, and it's a different job than
						the one media buyers were trained to do five years ago.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- LEAD FORM -->
			<section id="contact" class="contact-section">
				<div class="wrap">
					<h2>Get a second pair of eyes on your account</h2>
					<p class="contact-note">
						If two or more items in the audit above described your account, leave your email and a
						quick note. I read every one myself and reply personally.
					</p>

					<form id="meta-ads-lead-form" action="https://api.web3forms.com/submit" method="POST">
						<input type="hidden" name="access_key" value="0d5ededb-778b-452f-b8f0-72ebb2e4e461" />
						<input type="hidden" name="subject" value="New Meta ads help lead from jackmaguire.org/meta-ads-2026" />
						<input type="hidden" name="from_name" value="jackmaguire.org/meta-ads-2026" />
						<input type="checkbox" name="botcheck" class="botcheck" style="display:none" />

						<div class="form-row">
							<label for="lead-name">Your name<span class="req">*</span></label>
							<input type="text" id="lead-name" name="name" required autocomplete="name" />
						</div>

						<div class="form-row">
							<label for="lead-email">Email<span class="req">*</span></label>
							<input type="email" id="lead-email" name="email" required autocomplete="email" />
						</div>

						<div class="form-row">
							<label for="lead-message">What's going on with your account? (optional)</label>
							<textarea id="lead-message" name="message" rows="3" placeholder="Briefly, what's not working right now."></textarea>
						</div>

						<button type="submit" class="submit-btn">Send</button>
						<p class="form-note">No spam, no lists. I read every one myself.</p>
						<p class="form-success" role="status" hidden>Thanks, got it. I'll follow up by email.</p>
						<p class="form-error" role="alert" hidden>
							Something went wrong sending that. Please email
							<a href="mailto:maguirebaseball@gmail.com">maguirebaseball@gmail.com</a> directly instead.
						</p>
					</form>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- SOURCES -->
			<section class="sources-section">
				<div class="wrap">
					<p class="sources-note">
						Sources: CTC VP of Paid Media Tony Chopp, "How Meta Actually Works in 2026," eCommerce
						Playbook podcast, July 7 2026. Meta's engineering blog on Andromeda (December 2024) and
						GEM (November 2025). Jon Loomer's independent Meta ads analysis. Andrew Foxwell and the
						Foxwell x Motion 2026 State of Agencies report.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<footer class="plain-footer">
				<a href="/blog/">More writing</a>
			</footer>
		</main>

		<script>
			const form = document.getElementById('meta-ads-lead-form');
			if (form instanceof HTMLFormElement) {
				form.addEventListener('submit', async (event) => {
					event.preventDefault();
					const errorEl = form.querySelector('.form-error');
					const successEl = form.querySelector('.form-success');
					const submitBtn = form.querySelector('.submit-btn');
					if (submitBtn instanceof HTMLButtonElement) {
						submitBtn.disabled = true;
						submitBtn.textContent = 'Sending...';
					}
					if (errorEl instanceof HTMLElement) errorEl.hidden = true;

					try {
						const response = await fetch(form.action, {
							method: 'POST',
							headers: { Accept: 'application/json' },
							body: new FormData(form),
						});
						const result = await response.json();
						if (result.success) {
							form.hidden = true;
							if (successEl instanceof HTMLElement) successEl.hidden = false;
							return;
						}
						throw new Error(result.message || 'Submission failed');
					} catch (err) {
						if (errorEl instanceof HTMLElement) errorEl.hidden = false;
						if (submitBtn instanceof HTMLButtonElement) {
							submitBtn.disabled = false;
							submitBtn.textContent = 'Send';
						}
					}
				});
			}
		</script>
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	:global(body) {
		background: var(--paper);
	}
	main {
		max-width: none;
		padding: 0;
	}
	.wrap {
		max-width: 760px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 1.25em;
	}

	/* HERO */
	.hero {
		padding: 4em 0 3em;
		background: var(--paper-warm);
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.18);
	}
	.eyebrow {
		font-family: var(--font-heading), sans-serif;
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--accent-dark);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.06em;
		margin: 0 0 1em;
	}
	.hero h1 {
		font-family: var(--font-heading), sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(1.9em, 5.4vw, 2.7em);
		line-height: 1.15;
		margin: 0 0 0.9em;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	.hero-sub {
		font-size: 1.08em;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		max-width: 620px;
		margin: 0 0 2em;
	}
	.hero-stat {
		display: flex;
		align-items: baseline;
		gap: 1em;
		background: #fff;
		border: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.22);
		border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-dark);
		padding: 1.1em 1.3em;
		margin: 0 0 2em;
		max-width: 620px;
	}
	.stat-number {
		font-family: var(--font-heading), sans-serif;
		font-size: 1.8em;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--accent-dark);
		white-space: nowrap;
	}
	.stat-label {
		font-size: 0.92em;
		line-height: 1.5;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}
	.hero-cta {
		display: inline-block;
		font-family: var(--font-heading), sans-serif;
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 0.95em;
		background: var(--accent-dark);
		color: #fff;
		text-decoration: none;
		border-radius: 6px;
		padding: 0.8em 1.75em;
	}
	.hero-cta:hover {
		background: var(--accent);
	}

	/* LENS */
	.lens {
		padding: 2em 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.18);
	}
	.lens p {
		font-size: 0.98em;
		line-height: 1.65;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* SECTION SHARED */
	section h2 {
		font-family: var(--font-heading), sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(1.25em, 4.4vw, 1.6em);
		margin: 0 0 0.5em;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	.section-intro {
		font-size: 0.98em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		margin: 0 0 1.5em;
	}

	/* AUDIT */
	.audit {
		padding: 3em 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.18);
	}
	.audit-list {
		list-style: none;
		margin: 0 0 1.5em;
		padding: 0;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 1.25em;
	}
	.audit-list li {
		display: flex;
		gap: 1em;
		align-items: flex-start;
		background: #fff;
		border: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.16);
		border-radius: 8px;
		padding: 1.1em 1.25em;
	}
	.audit-mark {
		font-family: var(--font-heading), sans-serif;
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 0.85em;
		color: var(--accent-dark);
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		padding-top: 0.15em;
	}
	.audit-claim {
		font-weight: 700;
		margin: 0 0 0.35em;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	.audit-detail {
		font-size: 0.94em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.55;
	}
	.audit-result {
		font-size: 1em;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
		background: var(--paper-warm);
		border-radius: 6px;
		padding: 1em 1.25em;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.audit-result a {
		color: var(--accent-dark);
	}

	/* SYSTEMS */
	.systems {
		padding: 3em 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.18);
	}
	.systems-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 1.25em;
		margin: 0 0 1.5em;
	}
	.system-card {
		background: #fff;
		border: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.16);
		border-radius: 8px;
		padding: 1.25em;
	}
	.system-card h3 {
		font-family: var(--font-heading), sans-serif;
		margin: 0 0 0.2em;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	.system-role {
		font-size: 0.8em;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--accent-dark);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.03em;
		margin: 0 0 0.75em;
	}
	.system-card p:last-child {
		font-size: 0.94em;
		line-height: 1.55;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		margin: 0;
	}
	.systems-callout {
		font-size: 1.02em;
		line-height: 1.6;
		border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
		padding-left: 1em;
		margin: 0;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	.systems-callout .attrib {
		display: block;
		font-size: 0.82em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		font-weight: 400;
		margin-top: 0.4em;
	}

	/* PHASES */
	.phases {
		padding: 3em 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.18);
		background: var(--paper-warm);
	}
	.phase-list {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 1.25em;
	}
	.phase {
		background: #fff;
		border-radius: 8px;
		padding: 1.25em;
	}
	.phase-num {
		display: inline-block;
		font-family: var(--font-heading), sans-serif;
		font-size: 0.72em;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		background: var(--accent-dark);
		border-radius: 4px;
		padding: 0.25em 0.6em;
		margin: 0 0 0.6em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
	}
	.phase h3 {
		font-family: var(--font-heading), sans-serif;
		font-size: 1.05em;
		margin: 0 0 0.4em;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	.phase p {
		font-size: 0.92em;
		line-height: 1.55;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* VERDICTS */
	.verdicts {
		padding: 3em 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.18);
	}
	.verdict-table {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.6em;
	}
	.verdict-row {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 1em;
		padding: 1em 1.1em;
		border: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.16);
		border-radius: 8px;
		background: #fff;
	}
	.verdict-head {
		background: transparent;
		border: none;
		font-family: var(--font-heading), sans-serif;
		font-size: 0.75em;
		font-weight: 700;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		color: var(--accent-dark);
		padding: 0 1.1em;
	}
	.verdict-claim {
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 0.92em;
		color: rgb(var(--black));
	}
	.verdict-yes,
	.verdict-no {
		font-size: 0.86em;
		line-height: 1.5;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}
	.verdict-yes {
		border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
		padding-left: 0.75em;
	}
	.verdict-no {
		border-left: 3px solid #b3492f;
		padding-left: 0.75em;
	}

	/* SUMMARY */
	.summary {
		padding: 3em 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(85, 107, 47, 0.18);
	}
	.summary p {
		font-size: 1.05em;
		line-height: 1.65;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* CONTACT */
	.contact-section {
		padding: 3em 0;
	}
	.contact-note {
		font-size: 0.95em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		margin: 0 0 1.5em;
	}
	form {
